Company description:



Department of Energy, Environment and Climate Action



Job description:



The Artificial Intelligence (AI) Technical Specialist performs a critical strategic role in embedding and advancing AI practices into DEECA. With a strong customer first approach, the role is responsible for delivering AI solutions that prioritise automation, and enablement mindset.

Working in close partnership with ISD teams and key external stakeholders, the position will enhance and evolve the department's AI platform, while actively supporting both existing services and the development of new AI capabilities. The role requires a proactive change mindset, a commitment to continuous learning, and the ability to adapt to the dynamic landscape of AI technologies.

Specialist/Technical Expertise/Qualifications

Experience in designing and deploying AI/ML solutions in production environments.
4+ years of system administration experience with the Microsoft suite.
4+ years of system administration experience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure)
Experience in an Innovation setting
Excellent diagnostic, problem-solving, and communication skills with both technical and non-technical stakeholders

This is an ongoing position. The work location for this position is Melbourne CBD with hybrid work arrangements available.

To be considered for this position, applicants are encouraged to submit a resume and cover letter (no longer than 2 pages) summarising their skills and relevant experience.

Please refer to the Key Selection Criteria provided in the Position Description, including the mandatory requirements.

How to Apply:

If you are a current DEECA employee, please apply via DEECA Careers.

Click the ‘Apply' button and you'll be redirected to a new platform and create an account.

Applications close 11.59pm on Tuesday, 25 November 2025.

All applications must be submitted through the online portal. We are unable to consider email or manual applications at this time.

Other relevant information:

Preferred candidates will be required to undertake pre-employment screening, including a Declaration and Consent form and a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check.

To be eligible for appointment to this role, applicants will possess corresponding work rights for the advertised employment period. Appointment to an ongoing position is only available to an Australian/New Zealand citizen or an Australian Permanent Resident.

A Diverse, Inclusive and Flexible Workplace

DEECA welcomes applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds and we focus on the essential requirements of the job and being consistent and fair in our treatment of all applicants. We also understand that a balanced life is important to our employees. Talk to us about our flexible options such as working some days from home, starting early or late, working part time, job sharing or accessing paid or unpaid leave. For more information visit applying for a role with us.

Will you actively create a healthier future for tomorrow?

At Medibank we're encouraged to think big. We have a clear purpose to impact better health outcomes for our customers, patients and our community.

 

We celebrate diversity of thought because we want to make better decisions for our customers. As we work towards our goal of better health for better lives, we value the knowledge and contribution of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders. About the Role

We're seeking an experienced Data Solution Designer for an initial six-month contract engagement. This position is ideal for someone passionate about data, eager to learn, and capable of translating business requirements into practical, scalable solutions. The primary focus will be on data modelling and SQL, which is absolutely critical for success in this role.



You'll wear different hats—sometimes analysing data, sometimes designing models, and sometimes defining how solutions will work end-to-end. The right mindset, curiosity, and ability to learn are just as important as technical skills.



Key Responsibilities
Understand existing data solutions and design enhancements on top of them.
Develop end-to-end data solutions, including how data flows, where it's stored, and how it's presented.
Design data models using Kimball and Data Lake techniques.
Translate business requirements into clear technical specifications.
Investigate and analyse data to ensure accuracy and usability.
Document source-to-target data flows and perform data profiling.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to clarify requirements and communicate design decisions.
Work with cloud environments (AWS preferred) and modern data technologies.

What We're Looking For
Strong experience in data solution design or related roles.
Exceptional SQL skills (must-have), including advanced analytical functions.
Strong experience in data modelling and creating data marts.
Ability to analyse and interpret data effectively.
Exposure to cloud platforms (AWS ideal, others welcome).
Excellent communication skills to engage with business and technical teams.
Self-starter with strong initiative and investigative mindset.
Ability to wear multiple hats and adapt to changing priorities.

In this role, you'll be expected to quickly understand the existing solution and identify which hubs do what, then build on top of current designs while ensuring scalability and usability. Success will require strong problem-solving and analytical thinking—knowing where to start, what to do, and who to involve at each stage. If this sounds like you, we'd love to see your application come through!


A career with us


At Medibank, we believe work is something we do, not somewhere we go. Our modes of working - Collaboration, Connection and Concentration - help inform how your day is structured and where you choose to work will vary, depending on your role and requirements.  


The wellbeing of our employees is our priority. We encourage you to talk to us about any additional support you may require during the recruitment process, as well as how this role can be flexible for you. We encourage applications from candidates with a disability, if you require any adjustments or alternate formats of key information at any stage of the recruitment process, we welcome hearing from you.

About Us:

We are proudly owned by Auto & General Insurance Company. The A&G group is made up of trusted and well-known brands such as iSelect, Compare the Market and Budget Direct. In late 2024, iSelect and Compare the Market formed a new aggregation business within the A&G group that continues to support millions of Australians to compare and buy their personal finance, and household products such as insurance, energy, and loans.

The Opportunity:

Are you ready to elevate your career to the next level? We're seeking a Solution Architect to translate business requirements into implementable solution designs, evaluating options and providing clear rationale for the chosen approach. They will lead the definition and communication of the business, application, data, and technical vision, while documenting the solution’s structure and behaviour. With strong technical and stakeholder management skills, they shape future architecture and drive consensus for solutions that are both effective and supported. You’ll have the opportunity to:

Develop and maintain target state architectures and roadmaps aligned with business strategy and technology trends.
Analyse business requirements, constraints, and influencing factors to inform solution design.
Provide architectural leadership and ensure stakeholder alignment across business and technical teams.
Evaluate solution options from both technical and business perspectives to recommend best-fit approaches.
Deliver end-to-end architecture designs across business, data, application, and technology domains.
Support development teams in adopting new technologies and promoting sound architectural practices.
Define and uphold architectural best practices, ensuring solutions are scalable, secure, and fit for purpose.
Maintain strong stakeholder relationships, conduct architecture evaluations, and stay ahead of emerging ICT trends including cloud, APIs, and modern development frameworks.

Responsibilities: 

Design scalable, flexible solutions aligned with business needs using modern technologies (e.g. microservices, orchestration, data integration).
IT Strategy & Planning: Contribute to enterprise architecture roadmaps and ensure alignment of projects with architectural standards.
Enterprise Roadmaps: Define and present target architectures and migration plans; promote standardisation across IT.
Development Support: Guide teams on implementing architecture, resolving technical challenges, and ensuring delivery meets business KPIs.
Governance & Standards: Develop and maintain IT policies; support architecture reviews and advocate EA principles.
Collaboration & Knowledge Sharing: Work across teams to build capability and share expertise.
Stakeholder Engagement: Liaise with Security and Audit to ensure robust, secure solution designs.

Benefits:

At Compare the Market and iSelect we offer a dynamic and collaborative work environment where your talents will be recognised and rewarded. You’ll have the opportunity to make a meaningful impact and contribute to our continued success, we also provide:

Vibrant and social community who have annual celebrations, family fun days and regular events.
Enjoy flexible work arrangements, including the option of one day working from home each week or a 9-day fortnight.
Enjoy additional leave days - ‘ME’ leave and ‘Volunteer Day’ leave.
Employee discounts on Car, Home, Travel insurance.
Income protection insurance provided to support you in the event of non-work-related illness or injury.

About you:

Degree in an IT-related field is required; AWS/cloud and formal architecture certifications are advantageous.
4+ years as a Solution Architect across application, data, technology, and security domains.
2–3 years of experience in cloud technologies (AWS preferred), APIs, and modern development frameworks.
2–3 years in software development with strong integration and API expertise.
Experience in e-commerce (2+ years) and Martech/data technologies (1+ year) is a plus.
Strong communication, critical thinking, modelling, and risk analysis skills.
Customer-focused with excellent interpersonal and consensus-building abilities.
Proven consultancy skills across business analysis, IT architecture, infrastructure, cloud, and software design.

Want to know more? apply now!

At Compare the Market and iSelect and we’re proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and we embrace diversity.

This role is available to candidates with unlimited Australian working rights only.

Compare the Market and iSelect are committed to protecting your privacy. All applications and personal information are kept confidential and securely stored in line with Australian privacy laws, used only for recruitment purposes, and not shared with third parties outside the Auto & General Holdings Group without your consent.

Shape the Future of Data with Exposé

At Exposé, we're not just another consultancy—we're one of Australia's most respected names in Data, Analytics & AI. With teams across Adelaide, Brisbane, and Melbourne, we've built a reputation for solving some of the most complex data challenges in the country.


Our secret? A people-first culture. We believe happy consultants build the best solutions, and that's why our team of "Purple Peeps" love coming to work every day. We back this up with flexible work arrangements, cutting-edge projects, access to the latest tech, and a culture where collaboration and innovation thrive.

 

We are looking for an AI Engineer to design, build, and deliver practical AI solutions at enterprise scale. This role combines deep technical expertise with consulting skills to scope, architect, and operationalise AI systems. You will work across cloud platforms, generative AI, and agent-based workflows, collaborating with cross-functional teams to turn complex business challenges into usable, production-grade solutions.

 

Key Responsibilities

AI Solution Design & Delivery

Design, develop, and deploy AI solutions with a focus on Generative AI, Large Language Models (LLMs), Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), and agent-based workflows.

Architect cloud-native AI systems (Azure, AWS, GCP) with an emphasis on scalability, security, and cost efficiency using modern DevOps/LLMOps practices.

Implement robust agent workflows, including tool/function calling, guardrails, and state/memory management.

Configure, manage, and monitor OpenAI and Microsoft AI platforms, including license and usage optimisation.

Apply safety and governance controls to ensure reliable, ethical AI adoption.

 

Data Engineering & Integration

Build and manage scalable data engineering workflows using Databricks, including development and automation of notebooks for data processing, analytics, and ML pipelines.

Develop and optimise data pipelines, APIs, and integration layers to support enterprise AI/ML workloads.

Implement effective RAG patterns, including chunking, embeddings, and retrieval strategies.

Work with structured and unstructured data across SQL, NoSQL, and distributed systems.

Design and operate ETL/ELT processes, data transformations, and microservices-based data flows.

Ensure data quality, observability, and lineage across pipelines supporting AI applications.

 

Model Development & Operations

Fine-tune and operationalise AI/ML models using open-source and enterprise frameworks (LangChain, LlamaIndex, LangGraph, CrewAI, Hugging Face, OpenAI, etc.).

Apply basic machine learning techniques (classification, regression, clustering) for non-GenAI use cases where appropriate.

Integrate observability and monitoring tools for LLM and agent performance, tracing, and evaluation.

Contribute to CI/CD pipelines and manage codebases using GitHub, Azure DevOps, or similar platforms.

Stay current with advances in LLMOps, GenAI, and intelligent automation; recommend best-fit tools and approaches.

 

Consulting & Collaboration

Run discovery and design sessions to shape proofs-of-concept and MVPs.

Translate AI capabilities into clear business value propositions and roadmaps.

Communicate risks, assumptions, and dependencies to technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Collaborate with data engineers, developers, and business teams to deliver end-to-end solutions.

 

Key Skills & Experience

Experience: 4+ years building and delivering data-driven AI/ML systems in production.

Programming: Strong Python skills.

AI/ML & Frameworks: Experience with LLM/agent frameworks (LangChain, LlamaIndex, LangGraph, CrewAI), vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, pgvector), and basic ML modelling.

Data Engineering: Strong proficiency with Databricks and notebook-based development, SQL, NoSQL, ETL/ELT, data modelling, distributed systems, APIs (FastAPI, REST), and stream processing.

Collaboration Tools: Experience with Databricks, MLflow, Jira, Confluence, Azure DevOps.

Soft Skills: Strong written and verbal communication, business acumen, and the ability to bridge technical solutions with business needs.

 

What You’ll Gain

Exposure to enterprise-scale projects applying the latest AI and automation technologies.

Opportunities to develop in both technical depth and consulting breadth.

Career progression with ongoing learning and leadership development.

A collaborative, problem-solving environment where innovation and client impact are at the forefront.

 

Why Join Exposé?

·       Culture that's second to none – a team of respected industry leaders who support, challenge, and inspire each other.

·       Work on real impact projects with government, utilities, defence, healthcare and more.

·       Professional growth – development days, tech & training allowances, and opportunities to speak at industry forums.

·       Community focus – we actively support events, networks, and knowledge-sharing that raise the bar across the data industry.




If you're ready to engineer solutions that matter, grow alongside the best in the industry, and enjoy the journey while you're at it—we want to meet you.

Apply now and join the Purple Peeps in shaping the future of data in Australia.

At UTS, we're on a bold journey to become a leading public university of technology recognized for our global impact. Positioned at the cutting edge of creativity, innovation, and technology, we are dedicated to driving transformative breakthroughs that shape the future. Our state-of-the-art campus in Sydney's vibrant Tech Central precinct is alive with energy and ambition, creating a dynamic environment where curiosity and collaboration thrive.

About the Role

The Research Data Specialist (AI/ML) sits within the eResearch portfolio at UTS ITU and the National Coordination Business Unit at ARDC to support the ARDC's strategic objectives.

The AI Specialist will make a critical contribution to designing, developing, and deploying artificial intelligence and machine learning methods and solutions to solve complex problems and optimise business processes. They will collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify opportunities, gather data, build and train models, and implement solutions to enhance products, services, and operations.

This position is expected to drive change in an uncertain and highly dynamic, complex, competitive and global research and educational environment. It requires engagement and partnering with diverse groups of stakeholders in research-focussed environments and effective influencing of, and communication with, key stakeholders in cross disciplinary settings and across a broad range of research areas. The incumbent must maintain a keen proactive focus on contemporary issues related to Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) and apply this knowledge to develop innovative strategies and solutions.

About You

Excellent communication, including the ability to prepare documentation for various audiences, present, and to liaise, advise and negotiate at various levels.
Sound organisational and time management skills, including the ability to set priorities and perform well under pressure within a complex and changing environment.
Experience with successfully engaging with a diverse group of stakeholders within and across institutions, research facilities and/or research groups.
Knowledge of and experience with technologies and solutions that support data analysis, storage and publication, for example cloud computing solutions and research platforms and tools, with a particular focus on thought leadership, support, and promotion of artificial intelligence and machine learning.
A Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Artificial Intelligence, or a related field.
Significant relevant experience working in a research environment and a thorough understanding of the research process.

We are looking for a high-impact process improvement specialist who is able to lead and coordinate the adoption and integration of Microsoft Copilot across our client's wealth management practice. This is a 6-month full time contract position, with the opportunity for extension. We are also open to candidates on a day rate for this position.

Our client is a one of the largest banking and financial service businesses in Australia, who operate across all facets of banking and financial services. This position sits within their wealth management team which has approximately 200 staff. The wider business has gone through a major digital transformation and uplift with a focus on AI enablement and process improvement. This position is supporting the wealth management team's digital uplift.

You will identify use cases and opportunities for embedding automation into the wealth management team that is aligned with the strategy of the business - many use cases have been identified and must be delivered on. You will provide guidance, and recommendations on how to best tackle these initiatives.

Reporting to the Head of Transformation, there is a core user base of approximately 30 staff who you will be working closely with to get them familiar with the new tooling and change of process. Whilst this position is BAU focused it is also strategic, as tooling and process decisions will impact workflows and hiring decisions.

You will ideally understand banking and financial services (although this is not essential). It is essential that you have knowledge of process improvement using AI tooling (with a preference for Microsoft Copilot) and a passion for AI tooling and automation. An ability to manage change and digital transformation in teams is essential. You must have a tertiary qualification in business, technology or a related field - additional qualifications in AI will be highly advantageous.

If this position is taken on a full-time contract, there is a possibility that you will be involved in the roll out and training to the wider staff of 300. For more information please contact John Black on 0421 711 887 for a confidential discussion or apply through the portal to register your interest.

Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples are encouraged to apply.

Brunel has partnered with a leading resources company on a contract opportunity for a Data Analytics Engineer.

This role would suit someone who's highly motivated and eager to grow their skills in SAP and data products. You'll need strong experience working with SQL Server and Snowflake, and prior exposure to SAP PM/CMMS data or general familiarity with Heavy Mobile Equipment (HME) and the mining industry will be highly regarded.

Description

This role will focus on transforming complex SAP maintenance data into clear insights on performance of Heavy Mobile Equipment (HME) assets. Working within an engineering-led analytics team, you will use your expertise in Snowflake SQL, Python, and SAP data structures to design high-quality data models and pipelines to support advanced analysis that drives strategic decision-making towards decarbonisation initiatives.

You will play a key role in building the analytical backbone that will help engineering and maintenance stakeholders to access and interpret asset data. You will apply your skillset to transform and structure large, complex datasets - primarily from SAP PM/CMMS - into reliable and accessible information for analysis, reporting, and visualisation. You will work with an existing codebase in GitHub and help productionise existing proof-of-concept work.

The successful candidate will collaborate closely with external developers and internal technology teams to develop smooth data integration between front-end and back-end systems to ensure high-quality, reliable data foundations that enable confident performance insights. You will also develop Microsoft PowerBI and Excel tools to facilitate user data validation and transparency.

Key responsibilities include:

Develop and maintain Snowflake SQL data models and pipelines supporting asset performance analytics.
Clean, transform, and validate SAP maintenance, materials, and operational datasets for component reliability and lifecycle analysis.
Develop simple PowerBI and Excel reports to support subject matter expert review and user data validation.
Collaborate with technology teams and external application developers to enable efficient data access between systems.
Drive continuous improvement in data quality through investigation, testing, and proactive issue resolution.
Use GitHub for version control, code review, and collaborative development.
Maintain documentation, and governance across all analytical systems.

Profile

Degree in Engineering, Data Science, Computer Science, or a related technical discipline, or equivalent industry experience (3+ years) in data and analytics.
Strong proficiency with SQL Server / Snowflake and for data modelling, transformation, and automation (essential).
Proven experience working with SAP PM/CMMS data is strongly desirable.
Experience within Mining Heavy Mobile Equipment (HME) environment in maintenance, reliability, planning or engineering roles is strongly desirable.
Proficiency with Python, Microsoft PowerBI and Excel (desirable).
Familiarity with GitHub for version control, code review, and collaborative workflows.
Strong attention to detail, documentation skills, and commitment to data accuracy and traceability.
Demonstrated teamwork, communication skills and commitment to Health, Safety and Environment is essential

Ad Text:
About us

Tektalent has exclusively partnered with an Australian technology service provider that is taking the national market by storm, and is now apart of the largest technology group in the world, a billion dollar enterprise.

Our client offers a plethora of unique benefits & attractive notions to put them in a unique position of offering Managed services with a difference. Our client is genuinely dedicated to keeping the culture & morale of the team happy & fulfilled, whilst offering an environment to support customers with the latest & most innovative technology stacks.

This role is permanent & offers a flexible working environment to allow you the freedom to work from the office, or from the comfort of your own home. If you are stuck in a repetitive or mundane managed services environment where every day is the same, we can assure you that our client will change your perspective & give you a fresh new lease on working for a technology service provider, that genuinely cares about you & their customers. 

As a Level 3 Systems Engineer, you're the third line of support for their clients. This means going above and beyond in every interaction—responding quickly, solving problems with care, and showing clients that we’re committed to their success.




Qualifications & experience

5 + years experience in a Level 3 or level 2 + technical support / IT Support capacity

Technical breadth of experience across (You don't need deep experience in all, but at least exposure across the stack): Microsoft 365, Azure, VMware, Networking (Fortigate, Cisco, Unifi), Security (Defender, Sentinel), Storage & backup (Veeam, S3 (Wasabi, Azure), Windows Server 2012 - 2021

Advanced and complex understanding of Microsoft Modern Work knowledge environments (M365, Teams, Azure, InTune, Entra)

Clear communicator with strong customer engagement experience

Self-motivated & passion for technology / Customer service

Strong communication skills & ability to relate to people

Having experience working within an MSP (Managed Services) environment is highly attractive but not essential




Tasks & responsibilities

Act as a senior escalation point to the level 1 & 2 engineers, mentor & lead the way in resolving complex tickets & incidents

Regularly tests new ideas/technology in the labs & help the business evolve through AI & Automation to make your life easier

You apply strategic thinking to technical support. Every task you perform contributes to service quality, efficiency, and client trust

Actively contribute to the mentoring and development of team members, Develop processes and training for their practice

Respond to L3 support requests across M365, networking, backup, Azure and general IT stack (Microsoft & Windows)

Assist in executing the 100-day onboarding plan for new clients

Maintain ticket queues & updating clients on progress

Assist with Projects as required

Focus on customer satisfaction, solve complex problems, tailor solutions to meet customer needs, communicating strongly & with empathy

Support, deploy, manage, oversee & monitor systems, software & infrastructure

Engage in complex troubleshooting of client environments & being the liaison between the business & client's




Benefits

Personalized progression plan allowing you to branch into your desired area of interest / specialization whether it be cloud, cyber security, IT consulting or another specialization 

Certification and up-skilling is paramount, and you will get the investment to be at the forefront and technically as capable as possible 

Have access to unrestricted ability to troubleshoot your client's whole infrastructure environment

Have the opportunity to join the projects team on implementing solutions

Easily accesible location, close to public transport & away from the city traffic

Hybrid friendly work environment / flexible working

This business is owned by a billion dollar technology enterprise, giving them access to a global network of other businesses & state of the art systems & partnerships, also meaning stability, security & high growth

Automation / AI is invested in heavily by the business to automate the mundane tasks, which allows you to focus on the more exciting things

Market leading L&D program across MS certs / Vendor up-skilling

Business is heading into a new phase of stable & organic growth, opening up the door for opportunties for career progression within the business

Join a business that recognize high performance and have the ability to progress you into higher level roles very quickly

Hyper growth business meaning lots of opportunity for the team to learn, grow, develop with the business as they scale 

Bonus scheme which adds more money into your salary package

Work with a small portfolio of clients to ensure a focus on quality rather than quantity 

Weekly podcasts with the biggest names in tech - opportunity to network and meet the pioneers in the tech industry 

Experienced leadership team who knows how to run a well performing business 

Unique culture that is focused on individuality, personalization and having a lot of fun 

Flexible work options, no silly hours or overtime required 

One of the only MSP's that work with high profile enterprise clientele, which will allow you access to participating in high profile projects for these clients, these clients are both in the Public & Private sector

Talented engineering team led by the best in the industry, mentorship and ability to learn from the best is on offer 

Join one of Australia's leading Technology Success providers, taking managed services to the next echelon of service

Join a business offering a model beyond a standard MSP, offering the enrichment of technology through digital advisory, IT strategy, cloud computing, cyber security, unified communications & connectivity

Dedicated to adapting to innovation & being ahead of the curve, which allows you to have a genuine roadmap for growth & long term tenure

Culture of "Better together" & "celebrating success"

One of the best break-out areas to let your hair down with onsite arcade / DJ / Games area

A leadership team that genuinely cares about your wellbeing & happiness

Not just another mundane "MSP", they do things better & differently here, you will have to see & experience the difference for yourself

Tektalent is on a mission to set the standard for how recruitment should be done & belive our reviews tell the story, we look forward to reviewing your application.

About DBG Health:
DBG Health is a leading Melbourne-based health, wellness, and beauty company with over 1,500 professionals dedicated to making wellbeing accessible to all. Our diverse portfolio, spanning Arrotex Pharmaceuticals, VidaCorp Consumer Brands, Independent Pharmacies of Australia Group, Axe Health Services and MyDNA reflects our commitment to affordable, innovative solutions. Guided by our values of Pioneering, Accountability, Collaboration, and Tenacity (our PACT), we foster a high-performing, values-led culture where people grow, support each other, and go above and beyond for our customers. At DBG, we are Defined by Good, because helping people feel better isn't just our purpose, it's our responsibility.
 
Join DBG Health's New AI Team
 
We're building a brand-new in-house AI function to transform how we work, sell, and serve our customers. From data science and engineering to Power Platform development, you'll help design and deliver intelligent, automated solutions that make a real impact.
 
As a Machine Learning Engineer you'll design and manage data pipelines that connect systems, models, and tools, ensuring data flows are accurate, secure, and scalable. Working closely with data scientists and developers, you'll help build a powerful data ecosystem that turns insights into action across the healthcare and pharmaceutical space.
 
Role & Responsibilities:

Architect and design scalable data flows, integrations, and models connecting source systems, analytics, and front-end tools.
Build automated data pipelines for ingestion, transformation, and delivery, ensuring quality, lineage, and governance.
Deploy and maintain data solutions in production, supporting CI/CD and operational readiness.
Monitor performance, troubleshoot issues, and manage cost, access, and security across the environment.
Partner with technical and business teams, document environment design, and contribute to governance and compliance.
 Engage in continuous learning, maintain industry knowledge, and uphold safety and compliance standards.
Skills & Experience:

Proficient in Python, PySpark, SQL, and modern data engineering tools such as Azure Data Factory, Synapse, Fabric, and Delta Lake.
Skilled in building scalable batch and real-time pipelines, integrating diverse data sources, and managing end-to-end ETL workflows.
Experienced with CI/CD (Azure DevOps, Git), monitoring tools (Azure Monitor, Log Analytics), and API integrations (Microsoft Graph, REST).
Strong understanding of data quality, lineage, governance (Purview), and access control (RBAC, Entra ID).
Proven success partnering with data scientists and developers; exposure to pharmaceutical, healthcare, or life sciences environments.
Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field; Microsoft Certified: Azure/Fabric Data Engineer Associate.
Benefits & perks:
At DBG Health, we offer more than just a job - we offer a dynamic and supportive work environment where you can make a real impact. As part of our team, you'll have the opportunity to work alongside industry leaders, drive meaningful change, and grow both personally and professionally. DBG Health is Defined by Good. Our purpose is to create a world where feeling better is a right, not a privilege. Millions of people rely on us for access to affordable products and services that make them feel better. This is more than just a goal. It's our responsibility.

Exclusive discounts on our consumer health, wellness and beauty products - including MCo Beauty, E.L.F Cosmetics, Nude by Nature. Chemists Own and many more
Free membership to 28 by Sam Wood - 28 by Sam Wood is an online program designed to help Aussies get fit at home and live happier, healthier lives. From guided workouts and expert-created meal plans to motivational resources, it's designed for people of all fitness levels.
Generous parental leave scheme - ask us about it!
Access discounted private health insurance through Australian Unity, AIA Health of NIB
We are a values-driven business fostering a supportive and friendly team culture
Enjoy the ability to work autonomously, empowering you to drive your own success.
Convenient head office location close to public transport, cafes and restaurants
Opportunity to grow your career across all divisions within DBG Health - Arrotex Pharmaceuticals, VidaCorp Consumer Goods, Independent Pharmacies of Australia Group and Axe Health Services.
Ability to purchase additional leave to provide opportunity for employees to spend more precious time with family, travelling or even study
Explore the option of paying for your vehicle costs through novated leasing
DBG Health is committed to fostering a workplace culture that is safe and accessible for all. We are an equal- opportunity employer and encourage applications regardless of cultural background, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability or neurodiversity. We strive to build a collaborative, inclusive workplace that is representative of the communities we work and live in.

Group Description: We are seeking a detail-oriented and collaborative Strategy Technology Business Analyst to support the development and implementation of AI/ML and Generative AI solutions. The ideal candidate will act as a bridge between business and technical teams, ensuring that AI initiatives align with organizational goals and deliver tangible value. This role requires the ability to understand complex engineering concepts, communicate effectively with stakeholders, and manage standard Business Analyst responsibilities. We are looking for candidates with approximately 3-4 years of professional experience.







Project Description:

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather, analyze, and document business requirements for AI/ML and Generative AI initiatives.

Bridge the gap between business and technical teams by understanding and articulating complex engineering concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Conduct research and market analysis on AI/ML trends to support strategy development and identify opportunities for innovation.

Develop and maintain detailed project documentation, including business cases, process flows, and functional specifications.

Support the delivery of AI/ML solutions, ensuring alignment with business objectives, timelines, and best practices.







Key Skills: 

Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to translate business needs into technical requirements.

Foundational understanding of AI/ML and Generative AI concepts, with the ability to engage in detailed engineering discussions.

Proficiency in documentation tools and techniques, such as process modeling and requirement traceability.

Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills, capable of facilitating collaboration between technical and non-technical teams.

Familiarity with cloud AI platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure) and AI/ML implementation frameworks is a plus.







Location: Sydney or Melbourne or Brisbane







Benefits of working at Accenture:




·       18 weeks paid parental leave

·       Long & short-term career break opportunities

·       Structured career development program

·       Local and international career opportunities.

·       Certified as a Family Inclusive Workplace™

·       Flexible Work Arrangements - centered around Accenture’s Truly Human ethos and our commitment to supporting the health and wellbeing of our people.
